    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.37"/>
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>Red flowers scattered all over page</figDesc>
                </figure>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">37</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <add>3815 Mercier 
                        Kansas City, MO.</add><!--Aly's handwriting?-->
                
                        Feb 1. 1959.
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Poet,</salute></opener> <p>our mutual friend Margarette Ball Dickson tells me I may hope you will accept office of <hi rend="caps">POET LAUREATE OF MISSOURI CHAPARRALS</hi>. There will be no work in connection, however we wish to confer on you a membership. "Margie" as she is known, says make it "Life" but just now I am but Organizing Regent. I have much to learn, but I know that Chaparral Poets cover the world, in poetry, if not in membership, I am not sure, but think you hail from Nebraska, whe<del>e</del><add>r</add>e our Regional Director, Mildred Nye Dewey once called home.</p>
                
                <p>An<del>k</del><add>o</add>ther thing, I hope you can do for me. When I met you at the Kansas Seminar of Chaparrals, you mentioned one complete collection of yours that sold for $5. the poets could at that time buy. Think you were on the Emporia State Staff that summer, remember? Well, I failed somehow to get one. Is it possible to get one autographed ...yet? I started to send the money but on second thought want you to concentrate on giving full attention of "Yes" to first plea. <note type="authorial">see postal</note> 
                    <lb/>
                The truth is I am not sure the price postpaid to me.</p>
                
                <p>Two daughters and my son-in-law graduated from <hi rend="caps">M.U.</hi></p>
                
                <p>I am enclosing my first bulletin, and likewise my first job on the new duplicator. I do hope it comes out better and brighter next time.</p>
                
                <p>I shall be breathless until you reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute> 
                    
                    <signed>Viola Gardner</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi></opener> <p>Greetings to the wife.</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
